{"name":"Bolt","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/projectile-smoke-blue-light.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.QBm57hlOSWLmnk0I"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Bolt</em> sends damaging bursts of energy, streaks of holy light, or shards of matter toward one's foes.</p>\n<p>There are no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{Range} penalties, but the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{arcane skill roll} is affected by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Cover}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}, and all other usual @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties}.</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} of the <em>bolt </em>is 2d6, or 3d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Damage (+2): </span>The <em>bolt</em> causes 3d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} (4d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Disintegrate (+2): </span>If the <em>bolt </em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitates} a creature, it immediately dies and its body disintegrates. If the target is an object, everything in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template} disintegrates.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Bolt (+4):</span> The <em>bolt</em> causes 4d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} (5d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Rate of Fire (+2):</span> The <em>bolt </em>attack is made at @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rate of Fire]{Rate of Fire} 2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"2d6","range":"Smarts x 2","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Fire, ice, light, darkness, colored bolts, a stream of insects","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711051,"modifiedTime":1674268711051,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"2ZC6xxaxK8hfjp0G","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Protection","type":"power","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-crystal-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.KdYR8YGpA9b66t6U"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Protection</em> creates a field of energy or armor around a character, giving him 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{Armor}. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the bonus is applied to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} instead (and therefore immune to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{Armor Piercing} modifiers).</p>\n<p>Whether the protection is visible or not depends on the Trapping&mdash;this is entirely up to the caster.</p>\n<p><em>Protection</em> stacks with all other armor, natural or worn.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">SHIELD OTHER (+1):</span> When a character other then the one who cast this spell suffers one or more Wounds, the spellcaster can choose to take the Wounds instead. If the spellcaster does this, she get a free reroll on her Soak roll if she attempts a Soak roll.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"A mystical glow, hardened skin, ethereal armor, a mass of nanites","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711151,"modifiedTime":1674268711151,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"37Abx2a4yZI510hp","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Ward","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-carved-stone-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.7SOzdvd76jbjztbI"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A <em>ward</em> spell is a way of storing a single spell for activation under a predetermined trigger. <em>Wards</em> must be cast simultaneously with a single spell the caster knows that is activated when the <em>ward</em> is triggered.</p>\n<p><em>Wards</em> remain magically charged until activated, which requires a specific trigger. A trigger must contain no more than 10 words, and no more than two clauses. <em>Wards</em> aren't intelligent, and although they can recognize their caster they cannot distinguish between other individuals or races. Example triggers are, \"Activate when anyone but me opens that door,\" \"Activate when touched by anyone but me,\" \"Activate when I cry 'Help,'\" and so on.</p>\n<p>A hero may have a maximum number of <em>glyphs </em>cast at anyone time equal to half his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} die.</p>\n<p>Once triggered, the spell stored in the <em>ward</em> goes off as normal. It uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{traits} of the caster at the time of the glyph's creation. Once activated, the <em>ward</em> loses its magic. The caster of a <em>ward</em> , assuming he is alive, always knows when a <em>ward</em> has been triggered, regardless of distance, though not which specific <em>ward</em>.</p>\n<p><em>Wards</em> can be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{dispelled}, or removed with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} roll &ndash;2 (or &ndash;4 if cast with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}). The caster may erase a <em>ward</em> he has created simply by touching it and dissolving the magic (an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{action}). He may also temporarily negate a <em>ward</em> , thus allowing comrades to pass in safety but not those following him. Negating and reactivating a <em>ward</em> in this manner takes an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{action} each and requires the <em>ward</em> to be touched.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Alarm (+1):</span> For 1 additional Power Points, the <em>ward</em> creates a loud sound as loud as a thunder clap.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"Special","trapping":"Drawn or inscribed glyph, enchanted dragonshard  dust, arcane sigils.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711359,"modifiedTime":1674268711359,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"3lQAmVpWq0N99ALe","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Blessing","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.bgDPGCSwVjYYQ14A"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The people of the land depend on priests, shamans, and other caretakers to bless their communities. This powerful spell allows them to bless the crops, the children, and the beasts of the fields.</p>\n<p>The caretaker must spend an hour walking about the town and its fields, praying, chanting, sprinkling holy water, shaking sage, and otherwise asking for divine or magical aid. The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll is attempted afterwards.</p>\n<p>If failed, the caster must start over. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.hCxcCUCRxHOWcNGS]{Critical Failure}, the priest may not cast a <em>blessing</em> on these subjects again for one year.</p>\n<p>If successful, the area&rsquo;s crops come in hale and hearty, sickness and disease are rare, and couples are fertile and prosperous. The effects are relative. Casting <em>blessing</em> in a blighted land may only raise a community to subsistence-level</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"10","damage":"","range":"One town/community","duration":"One Year","trapping":"Prayers, chanting, festivals","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711234,"modifiedTime":1674268711234,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"4GLAOZgEkiGeY3wA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mind Wipe","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/control/sihouette-hold-beam-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.V2wPVX46INIpt8yB"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Mind wipe </em>removes a target's memories, a terrible violation in most civilized societies. The power is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by a victim's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} and requires a full minute of mental struggle. The victim must be conscious during this time, so if not restrained he can simply move out of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range}.</p>\n<p>If @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful}, the victim forgets a single event (up to about 30 minutes of time). A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} removes a complex memory of several hours.</p>\n<p>If the defender wins, the caster cannot affect him with <em>mind wipe </em>for 24 hours. (Others may reattempt the power, however.)</p>\n<p>The memory remains missing but strong evidence that challenges its &ldquo;logic&rdquo; allows a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} roll at &minus;2 to remember fragments determined by the DM.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Edit (+1): </span>Instead of wiping the memory, the caster edits it as she sees fit.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Fast Cast (+2): </span>The caster can wipe a memory as an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{action}.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Mind Wipe (+2): </span>The effect completely removes a single event, person, place, thing, etc., from the victim's memory.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A noxious drink, parasites, touching the target's temples","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711343,"modifiedTime":1674268711343,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"4blgE58lNmwLNvFu","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Object Reading","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/holy/chalice-glowing-gold.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.CYSTHbkYJSwq3xps"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Object reading </em>is the ability to get visions of the past from an object. With a successful casting, she gains a vague impression of whatever information she's looking for, from the object's creation forward. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} grants her more specific information.</p>\n<p>If the caster uses <em>object reading</em> on a bloody knife to investigate a murder, for example, success might tell her the wielder was a human and that the attack happened at night. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, she might get a glimpse of the killer's face or some other clue that to reveal his identity.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Projection (+2): </span>The caster may broadcast the vision, projecting it out into a space the size of a small room. Anyone present may see and hear the events and examine the projection from all angles.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","trapping":"Touching the object, glowing hands","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711282,"modifiedTime":1674268711282,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"4zUd15DhfkBScsv8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Growth/Shrink","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/control/silhouette-grow-shrink-tan.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"gm-notes":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.ojz4SSvXHyOfoOjU"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Growth </em>increases the recipient's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} by 1 for every 2 Power Points spent. Each increase in Size grants the target a one-step increase to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength} and 1 point of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness}. This does not increase @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wounds} regardless of change to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}.</p>\n<p><em>Shrink </em>reduces the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} of the subject one step for every 2 Power Points spent to a maximum of Size &minus;2 (approximately the size of a cat). Each step reduced decreases @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength} one die type (minimum of d4) and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} by 1 (minimum of 2).</p>\n<p>For unwilling targets, the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+2): </span>The power's Duration is measured in minutes per rank instead rounds.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+2): </span><em>Shrink only. </em>The target of <em>shrink</em> may retain her normal @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} while small.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Gestures, words of power, potions","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711266,"modifiedTime":1674268711266,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"50ZQkfzq2XmGiGw4","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Blast","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/fire/explosion-mushroom-nuke-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.xJxrn9AfGtpqfhll"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Blast</em> launches a ball of explosive energy or matter. The area of effect is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. Every target within suffers 2d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage}, or 3d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Area Effect Attacks}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+0/+1): </span>The caster can focus the blast to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template} for no extra cost, or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +1.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Damage (+2): </span>The <em>blast</em> causes 3d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} (4d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Blast (+4): </span>The <em>blast</em> causes 4d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} (5d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"2d6","range":"Smarts x 2","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Balls of fire, ice, light, darkness, colored bolts, swarm of insects","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711230,"modifiedTime":1674268711230,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"6SBxLqcxwvswsnOt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mystic Intervention","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/holy/chalice-glowing-gold-water.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qmkdk1c7wo","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Legendary","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.v9yEHCDLrRQNSNKN"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Sometimes even a wizard&rsquo;s best spell or a cleric&rsquo;s greatest miracle isn&rsquo;t enough. In times of great need, casters must turn to greater powers than their own and ask a patron to take a personal hand in the affairs of mortals.</p>\n<p><em>Mystic intervention</em> allows a caster to trigger a great event of some sort. The event should be epic in proportions, such as saving a city from a siege, causing an earthquake to level a city, raising a legendary creature such as the Century Beast, bringing a centuriesdead hero to life, or closing the gate to some terrible and otherworldly dimension.</p>\n<p>The caster must stand in a magical ring, divine circle, sacred site, or other place of power and use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.yteAvhzlGurAsrTr]{Ritual Magic} rules to cast. (Power Points are listed for that purpose&mdash;it can never be cast without ritual magic.)</p>\n<p>If successful, he&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.tGBCnKkDi55VRxgm]{Exhausted} for the next five days but some version of the desired effect, narrated by the Dungeon Master as she sees fit, happens with a great display of magical energy.</p>\n<p>If the ritual&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.712V5zxIGyc8K10r]{Dramatic Task} fails, the caster is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.tGBCnKkDi55VRxgm]{Exhausted} as above and may not attempt the ritual again for five days or until some narrative goal is met (finding rare replacement components, the conjunction of the moons, or whatever the DM feels is appropriate). A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.hCxcCUCRxHOWcNGS]{Critical Failure} also causes 5d6 damage in a 20&rdquo; (40 yard) radius as well.</p>\n<p><em>Mystic intervention</em> should give the heroes respite from major events but shouldn&rsquo;t short circuit the Dungeon Master&rsquo;s entire campaign. For example it may not slay a powerful foe outright, but may provide a weapon that aids in the fight against it. Or a besieging army might be swept away by a great flood&mdash;but another approaches in a month. The city of a great enemy might be leveled by an earthquake, but the citizens begin to rebuild mere hours afterwards.</p>\n<p>Finally, the power can&rsquo;t override free will. It can&rsquo;t make a good person evil, fall in love with someone they&rsquo;re not, or otherwise change their nature. It might give an individual new perspective or a moment of empathy somehow, but true change is always a choice.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Legnedary","pp":"20","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"Special","trapping":"Prayer, rituals, sacrifices, special artifacts or relics.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711015,"modifiedTime":1674268711015,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"6Uc9jO8l7jzEZoP8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qmkdk1c7wo","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Legendary","color":"#000000","name":"Legendary","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_e37lp7g17kg"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["6Uc9jO8l7jzEZoP8","yJBvKufi1V2sWiLf"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","system":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipStatus":1,"isArcaneDevice":false,"arcaneSkillDie":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"powerPoints":{},"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"category":"","damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"parry":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false,"trademark":0,"isHeavyWeapon":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711025,"modifiedTime":1674268711029,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"6dWRkk8GcZLqi614"}
{"name":"Entangle","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-entangle-foot-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.ful8IniWqVVlMrP9"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Entangle </em>allows the caster to restrain a target with ice, bands of energy, or other vine-like @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trappings}. If successful, the target must @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Evasion]{Evade} or become @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Entangled}. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, he's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound}.</p>\n<p>Victims may break free on their turn as detailed under @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound and Entangled} with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness}&nbsp;of 8.</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+2/+3): </span>For +2 Power Points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} or use the Stream Template.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Damage (+2): </span>Entangled targets take 2d4 damage at the end of their turn.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Deadly (+4): </span>Entangled targets take 2d6 damage at the end of their turn.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Tough (+3): </span>The <em>entangling</em> material is particularly resilient. Rolls to break free are made at &minus;2 and it's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} increases to 10.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Glue bomb, vines, handcuffs, webs.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711106,"modifiedTime":1674268711106,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"6suWmcer60mQYcS1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000","name":"Seasoned","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_e37lp7g17kg"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["ZkUfmGOP9Gq6Z4TF","kf1O4venRtMuCThE","6SBxLqcxwvswsnOt","4GLAOZgEkiGeY3wA","gFUR4kXPxYQvHsL1","oVdxR8KBpAx6yANH","RkyLQqCKPALiTssP","vhfkpWfO5gEc0rqC","undU5Bc4pj3ZkQCD","m33DosLBD2jojMKg","igKE6HhqRP4HjLpF","50ZQkfzq2XmGiGw4","vmroBerFvOLZHDr0","fAAc8NHKYjI7Z4DR","OyywhbnaZ1GlZCWL","4zUd15DhfkBScsv8","j8s9gUoYWD9fj01l","iwhsfUJibdpljS0E","JWOHH4k0G3r4S2X2","uKF2SSx39KYm3gDP","TS8nEIYw79AbLO4B","FmvfDsQyXCSIQ8l5"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","system":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipStatus":1,"isArcaneDevice":false,"arcaneSkillDie":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"powerPoints":{},"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"category":"","damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"parry":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false,"trademark":0,"isHeavyWeapon":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711309,"modifiedTime":1674268711315,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"7CjDPtahL3ngSHzH"}
{"name":"Planar Binding","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circle-ouroboros.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.181xBGsAWjfIYV22"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Planar binding</em> allows a caster to summon and contain a creature from another plane to a trap of some sort, such as a binding circle, pentagram, mystic circle, etc. The trap is created with chalk, salt, paint, glyphs and wards, or other materials prior to the power's activation, and takes ten minutes of time to prepare.</p>\n<p>Once the trap is prepared, the summoner states what type of extra-planar creature she wishes to bind. She must know about the creature somehow, perhaps by previous encounter, access to strange books and scrolls, or an Occult roll with a bonus or penalty set by the Dungeon Master depending on the creature. The summoner can even summon a specific entity if she knows its proper name.</p>\n<p>Casting is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} between the summoner's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} and the entity's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}. If the entity wins, the spell fails and the entity knows who attempted to bind it. If the caster rolls a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, the creature may appear if it chooses to and is unbound&mdash; it may do as it wishes and its abilities allow.</p>\n<p>If the caster wins, the creature is summoned into the trap and magically bound there until it agrees to perform a service for the caster or breaks free (see below). The Power Points used to bind the target are invested and unavailable until the creature breaks free or is released.</p>\n<p>The summoner may free the entity as a free action anytime she chooses, regardless of sight, distance, or other factors. When she does so, she decides if it remains on her plane or returns to whichever plane it was summoned from.</p>\n<p><strong>Bargaining:</strong> Casters summon creatures to task them with a \"service\" of some sort, such as taking part in a difficult battle, acting as a bodyguard, or performing some task the caster can't or doesn't want to perform herself. The negotiation can usually be handled through roleplaying (and perhaps a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} roll).</p>\n<p>Cunning creatures require more incentive. An evil being might ask for time to wander the earth and wreak havoc, a sacrifice, or some other \"devil's bargain\" proportional to the service required. A good or noble creature might aid the summoner without reward if the cause is just, or might require she perform some task for her followers or sphere of influence. Entities never agree to services they can't perform or that will clearly result in their destruction.</p>\n<p>Once the creature agrees to the terms, it must carry them out to the best of its ability. The caster does not have to live up to any promises she set&mdash;though entities might seek revenge if deceived or their kind are summoned too often. Casters must be wary of this, especially if the beings have a way back to the prime material plane!</p>\n<p><strong>Breaking Free:</strong> If no agreement is made after 24 hours, the caster must renew the mystic bonds by making another @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} versus the creature's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}. This continues every 24 hours until an agreement is reached or the creature breaks free. The entity can't use any other power or ability to escape.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"8","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A summoning circle, an enchanted, iron casket, magical chains.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711347,"modifiedTime":1674268711347,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"7ouX6M14F4XTBnvE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Animate War Tree","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/nature/tree-animated-strike.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_y6l3qfj0w3","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.o9pXdUx2sxDTy4nA"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>War trees are semi-sentient, animated trees, created usually only in desperate times of need.</p>\n<p>With a success, the hero awakens one tree (which must be taller than 30') he is touching as a war tree. On a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the animated tree is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}. At the end of the spell's duration, the war tree transforms back into a regular tree. If the war tree is killed before this time, the spell is automatically ended.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"10","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Tree becomes covered in runes, warps into a \"tree man.\"","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268710991,"modifiedTime":1674268710991,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"7vEypESjFOGQX3cG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Healing","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-area-circle-red-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.I0mcegEN4B92V3gq"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Healing </em>removes @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} less than an hour old. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} removes one Wound, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} removes two. The power may be cast additional times to remove additional Wounds within that hour and as long as the healer has enough Power Points.</p>\n<p>For @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}, the DM must first determine if the ally is still alive (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Healing]{Aftermath}). If so, a successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll returns the ally to action (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} if it matters).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Healing (+10): </span><em>Greater healing</em> can restore any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, including those more than an hour old.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Crippling Injuries (+15): </span>The power can heal a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Injury Table]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation}). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails}, this caster cannot <em>heal </em>that particular injury (but somoene else may try). If successful, the subject is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} for 24 hours.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Mass Healing (+2/+3): </span>For a +2 Power Points, healing affects all allies within a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster (or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +3).</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Neutralize Poison or Disease (+1): </span>A successful <em>healing </em>roll negates any @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Poison]{poison} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Disease]{disease}. If the poison or disease has a bonus or penalty associated with it, the modifier applies to the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll as well.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Laying on hands, touching the victim with a holy symbol, prayer","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711122,"modifiedTime":1674268711122,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"AWM9Vdtf63vJKHji","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Accelerate Healing","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/life/cross-beam-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.DaW4KyBqCojXGCSC"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The power accelerates the target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Healing]{natural healing} rate. With a successful casting the target may make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Healing]{natural healing} roll once every 24 hour period, with a +2 bonus if cast with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. With a success, the target also gains a +2 bonus to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} rolls for resisting @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Disease]{disease} during the same time, and a +4 bonus with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. The target may only be affected by one casting of accelerate healing at a time.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"24 hours","trapping":"Mystical sense, spiritual advice, gestalt knowledge","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Lankhmar"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711321,"modifiedTime":1674268711321,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"BUkpuDW0PTiQLmHH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Smite","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-sword-steel-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.hUoU4cSN6b5UmO4f"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This power is cast on a weapon of some sort. If it's a ranged weapon, it affects one entire magazine, 20 bolts, shells, or arrows, or one full &ldquo;load&rdquo; of ammunition (the DM determines the exact quantity for unusual weapons). While the power is in effect, the weapon's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} is increased by +2, or +4 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Limitations:</strong> In the case of smite with a Personal Limitation, &ldquo;Self&rdquo; refers to the specific weapon instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Smite (+2): </span>The weapon's damage is increased by +4, or +6 (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage}) with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Spiritual Weapon (+2): Instead of enchanting a weapon, the spellcaster creates a weapon of pure energy. This weapon activates on the casters turn and may attack as a limited action with Fighting equal to the caster's arcane skill. The weapon does Spr+d4 damage (Spr+d6 with a raise).</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"A colored glow, runes, sigils, crackling energy, barbs grow from the blade","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711175,"modifiedTime":1674268711175,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"CI0OA3mGrodwBNMi","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Summon Beast","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/deer-movement-leap-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.IUYu8TFx6wAlBU0t"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Animals have long been associated with wizards, whether it be the familiars of witches or the fetish beasts of shamans. <em>Summon Beast</em> allows a user to summon mundane animals.</p>\n<p>A character may learn this spell while a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Novice}, but cannot summon any larger creatures until he attains the appropriate @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank}. It materializes anywhere in Range, and with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll, it's @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Resilient]{Resilient} as well.</p>\n<p>The beast acts on its creator's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} and follows her basic commands to the best of its ability.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 119px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<th class=\"main-heading\" style=\"height: 17px;\" colspan=\"3\">Summon Beasts</th>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\" style=\"height: 17px;\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\" style=\"height: 17px;\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\" style=\"height: 17px;\">Servant</th>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">Novice</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">1 small animal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">Seasoned</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">1 medium animal or swarm of rats, birds, insects, or other vermin, or 2 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">Veteran</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">6</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">1 large, 2 medium or swarms, or 4 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">Heroic</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">1 huge, 2 large, 4 medium or swarms, or 6 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">Legendary</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">10</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; text-align: center;\">2 huge, 4 large, 6 medium or swarms, or 8 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Small creatures have a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} less than zero. Medium creatures are Size +0 to Size +3. Large covers Size +4 to +7, and Huge is +8 or larger. Swarms share a similar set of statistics and fill a Medium Burst Template.</p>\n<p>The beast is under the total control of the summoner for the Duration of the spell.</p>\n<p>Animals can only be summoned in their natural terrain. So while a wizard may be able to summon a swarm of rats in Sharn, only on the open plains can he call a lion to his side.</p>\n<p>Summoned creatures appear from the nearest appropriate terrain. For instance, rats swarm out of sewers, a lion emerges from jungle or grass on the savannah, and a swarm of birds descends from the clouds or erupts from the trees. If in doubt, assume the beasts \"appear\" 1d10 x 2 yards away from the caster. When the Duration expires, the animal leaves of its own accord.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><strong><em>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</em></strong></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+1): </span><em>Summon beast's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Increased Trait (+1): </span>The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 Power Point. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mind Rider (+1): </span>The caster can communicate and sense through the beast.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Animal bones or feathers of appropriate sort, glyphs, chanting.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711198,"modifiedTime":1674268711198,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"CIcpUlYqQ5eKwmar","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Light/Darkness","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/torch-fire-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.e1hYvaHFu8ErAb8J"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in an area the size of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Area Effect (+2):</span> The <em>light</em> expands to the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">True Darkness (+2):</span> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mobile (+1):</span> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Illusionary torch, sunlight, darkness, thick fogs","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711134,"modifiedTime":1674268711134,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"CWMGKcue8XeAWSxn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Burst","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/fire/projectile-wave-arrow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.mK0tJHKFKIeyarLg"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Burst </em>produces a large fan of energy that bathes its targets in red-hot fire, a cone of cold, or other damaging matter or energy.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} creates a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} or Steam Tempalte starting at the caster and extending outward. Everything within suffers 2d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} (or 3d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Damage (+2):</strong> The <em>burst</em> causes 3d6 damage, or 4d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><strong>Greater Burst (+4):</strong> The <em>burst</em> causes 4d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} (5d6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"2d6","range":"Cone Template","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A shower of flames, light or other matter of energy.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711066,"modifiedTime":1674268711066,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"DryTtF2maJmXoAko","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Fly","type":"power","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/moulinette/tiles/custom/icons-custom/feats/feats/acrobatic.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.RpUCNr85rPqFozCX"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Fly </em>allows a character to soar at @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} 12&Prime;, or twice that with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} (he may not @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Run}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+2): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 2 additional Power Points each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Swift Flight (+5): </span>The base flying Pace increases to 24 (60 MPH), or 48 (120 MPH) with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Gusty winds, wings, broomsticks","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711336,"modifiedTime":1674268711336,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EgTlCqY3ULISQemx","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Confusion","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.rTXb5MNFDz1d3CkZ"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Confusion </em>confounds all targets in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} , making them either @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable}, or both with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. The same effect applies to all those affected. These states are removed at the end of the victims' next turn as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+0/+1): </span>The caster can focus the <em>confusion </em>to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template} for no extra cost, or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +1.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Confusion (+2): </span>On a success, targets are @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} in addition to being @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} (or both with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}). <em>Confusion </em>is a non-damaging effect and cannot cause a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} on an already @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} target.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Hypnotic lights, brief illusions, loud noises.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711070,"modifiedTime":1674268711070,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EuWQSBTXW0U6EuSl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Zombie","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/death/hand-dirt-undead-zombie.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.DTbVXVhrP959vdV3"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Zombie </em>grants animation and basic intelligence to the remains of a once-living being. The summoned horror is obedient but literal-minded in its duties. It isn't telepathic, and must be controlled by voice.</p>\n<p>The being has the physical skills it had in life, but its @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}, and related @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{skills} are reset to d4. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{casting roll} increases any one of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Traits} by one die type (caster's choice).</p>\n<p>Corpses aren't summoned by this ability, so there must actually be a supply of bodies in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} (DM's call).</p>\n<p>An undead @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} by damage can't be raised with this power again.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Zombies (+1): </span>A larger horde can be raised in a single casting by paying an additional 1 Power Point for each extra <em>zombie</em> raised.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Armed &amp; Armored (+1 per Zombie): </span>The dead rise with +2 armor and weapons common to their background or environment. Choose one:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hand Weapon:</strong> Str+d6</li>\n<li><strong>Ranged Weapon:</strong> Range 12/24/48, Dmg 2d6</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mind Rider (+1/+3): </span>The caster can communicate and sense through one of the undead he's conjured. If it's destroyed, he may jump to any of the others currently under his control. For 3 Power Points, Mind Rider affects all the zombies created in this summoning.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Permanent (0):</span>The zombie is given unlife until @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} by Wounds. The Power Points used to raise it are &ldquo;invested&rdquo; and unavailable until it's destroyed. The necromancer may terminate his creations' unlife at any time, regardless of sight, distance, or other factors. His Power Points then begin recharging normally.\n<p>Permanent zombies remain animated even if their creator is slain!</p>\n</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Skeletal (+1 per Zombie): </span>The corpse sloughs off the anchor of dead flesh and rises as a skeleton. This increases its @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} dice by one die type each.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Zombie Creatures</strong></h3>\n<p>Animals and other creatures can also be raised with this foul ability! The cost is 2 for a creature of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} &minus;1 or &minus;2, 3 for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} 0, and 1 for a Small @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarm}, 2 for a Medium Swarm, or 3 for a Large Swarm.</p>\n<p>Larger creatures cost 3 + @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} in Power Points. For example, an undead grizzly (Size 2) costs 5 Power Points to raise.</p>\n<p>Magical or supernatural @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bestiary]{Special Abilities} aren't conferred to the undead form, but those inherent to the creature are, such as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Frenzy]{Improved Frenzy}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach}, a swarm's attack, etc.</p>\n<p>Additional zombie creatures cost half their base cost if raised at once, instead of the +1 listed for <strong>Additional Zombies</strong> (round up, minimum of 1).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<h3><strong>Zombie</strong></h3>\n<p>These walking dead are typical groaning fiends looking for fresh meat.</p>\n<p><strong>Attributes:</strong> Agility d6, Smarts d4, Spirit d4, Strength d6, Vigor d6</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d6</p>\n<p><strong>Pace:</strong> 4; <strong>Parry:</strong> 5; <strong>Toughness:</strong> 7</p>\n<p><strong>Edges:</strong> &mdash;</p>\n<p><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Bite/Claws:</strong> Str.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless}:</strong> Zombies are immune to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Ability (Undead)]{Undead}:</strong> +2 Toughness; +2 to recover from being Shaken; no additional damage from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots}; ignores 1 point of Wound penalties; doesn't breathe; immune to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Disease]{disease} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Poison]{poison}.</li>\n<li><strong>Weakness (Head):</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots} to a zombie's head do the usual +4 damage.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Carving symbols on corpses, throwing bones, graveyards, \"leather\" books","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711362,"modifiedTime":1674268711362,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FADQSqpXlioUX8lP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Warrior's Gift","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/melee/hand-grip-sword-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.9GSvLl5s9aJIOSyK"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll, the recipient gains the benefits of a single Combat @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Edges]{Edge} chosen by the caster. The caster (not the recipient) must have the same @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank} or higher as the Edge's Requirements. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the recipient gains the Improved version of the Edge (if there is one, and even if he doesn't meet the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Rank Requirement}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+4): </span>The recipient gains two Combat Edges at once.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"4","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Gestures, prayer, whispered words, concentration","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711306,"modifiedTime":1674268711306,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FmvfDsQyXCSIQ8l5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Wall Walker","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/invertebrates/spider-web-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.gGgeoMVnqCjbE9cy"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Wall walker </em>allows the recepient to walk on vertical or horizontal surfaces. With @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, she moves at half her normal @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace}. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, she may move at full @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} and even @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{run}.</p>\n<p>If forced to make an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll to climb or hang on to the a surface, she adds +4 to the total.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Spider-like visage, prickly hairs on hands and feet","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711209,"modifiedTime":1674268711209,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FvKggNP34UEmq12F","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Plane Shift","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/earth/orb-ringed-lava-black-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.3N3J1fzOpvc3rIbc"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Plane shift</em> allows the caster to move directly to another plane of existence (see page 163). If plane shifting to a known location, a success indicates the target appears within 10d10 miles of the intended location. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the mage appears half that distance away.</p>\n<p>If the caster doesn't know exactly where he wants to go, he can research locations within that plane to target a specific city, geographic location, etc. Failure means he arrives at a completely random location on that plane. Success puts him in the general vicinity, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} puts him closer to the desired locale. This is in addition to the accuracy of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Extra-Dimensional Space (+1): </span>Instead of traveling to a known plane, the recipient travels to a pocket dimension where he's conjured a magical shelter or similar structure with basic necessities, food, and water for up to five people. The structure remains afterward, so the mage and his companions may return to it as desired.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Transport Foe (+2): </span>The caster sends an unwilling target to another plane or extra-dimensional space. The being resists the casting with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll, at &minus;2 if the caster made his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll with a raise. If failed, he's transported to another plane of the caster's choice for five rounds before returning (or as close as possible if the space is occupied).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"A summoning circle, an enchanted, iron casket, magical chains.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711350,"modifiedTime":1674268711350,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"G6DfUlcmZ3CTt4PA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Baleful Polymorph","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-explode-disintegrate.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.kSJnpOlrMKSUydSZ"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Choose a creature with the Humanoid type, from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} &ndash;2 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} 3. <em>Baleful polymorph</em> is an opposed roll of the character's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} versus the target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}. With a success, the victim changes into a relatively harmless creature. They gain the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor}, and innate abilities of the animal, but retain their own @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}.</p>\n<p>Power point cost is a base of 3 plus 2 per point of size change.</p>\n<p>The target must be able to survive in its current environment while in its new form (you cannot turn someone into a fish while on dry land). If the victim critically fails the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll, they gain the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} of the animal as well, believing that they are an animal until the power ends. At the end of each of the victim's subsequent turns, he can make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll at &ndash;2 (&ndash;4 if the caster got a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) to return to his normal form.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+2): </span>The power's Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Cursed artifact, a bolt of energy","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Savage Pathfinder"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711324,"modifiedTime":1674268711324,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"GNcdLCVCUV3VMxcI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Banish","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.ndX0m9xUnnldbMZH"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Banish </em>sends entities from immaterial planes back to their native dimensions. This includes ghosts, demons, elementals, and similar beings (at the DM's discretion).</p>\n<p><em>Banishing </em>a being is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} versus the target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the target is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}, and each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} causes a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}.</p>\n<p>If this @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitates} the target it returns to its native plane of existence. <em>Banished </em>entities may return when the Dungeon Master feels it's appropriate, such as the next full moon, when summoned again, or even a few rounds later if it's a particularly powerful creature under the right conditions or in a location of power.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+1/+2/+3): </span>For +1 Power Point the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template}. For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Holy items, arcane symbols, handful of salt","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711328,"modifiedTime":1674268711328,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"HAJSvvFOG5K69VUv","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Illusion","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/magical/fae-fairy-winged-glowing-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.4kumVVllaE3s46om"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Illusion </em>can be used to create a visual scene or replica of most anything the caster can imagine, but it is silent, intangible, and incapable of affecting the real world. For example, illusionary weapons pass through foes, one cannot sit in an illusionary chair, and an illusionary dog has no audible bark.</p>\n<p>Those who contact an <em>illusion </em>or doubt it's real make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} roll as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} (at &ndash;2 if the power was activated with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}). If @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful}, that individual is no longer subject to this casting.</p>\n<p>The DM should make @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{group rolls} for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} as they point out the <em>illusion's </em>inconsistencies to each other.</p>\n<p>The volume of the <em>illusion </em>must fit within a sphere the size of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} (4&Prime; or eight yards in diameter).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area Effect (+1):</strong> The illusion's area of effect is increased to the size of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><strong>Deadly Illusion (+3):</strong> The <em>illusion</em> may attack or otherwise cause harm. Once per turn, the caster may use an action to &ldquo;attack&rdquo; an individual. This is an opposed roll of the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} versus the target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} (at &minus;2 if the power was activated with a raise).\n<p>If the caster wins, the target is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} (this cannot cause Incapacitation). With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the target suffers a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} (this can cause Incapacitation). The caster may attack additional foes as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Actions}. She may not use other combat maneuvers, such as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attacks} (though it may look that way!)</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> The Duration is measured in minutes.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobility (+1/+2):</strong> For a +1 Power Point, the <em>illusion</em> can move (and fly) at a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} of 12, or 24 for +2 Power Points. This is a limited @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action}.</li>\n<li><strong>Sound (+1):</strong> The power generates sound appropriate to the <em>illusion</em>. Illusionary allies may talk, illusionary crows caw, and so on. It may not mask or mute existing sound, however. </li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+2):</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} rolls to disbelieve the <em>illusion </em>are made at &minus;2. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Magical spells, holograms, \"ethereal materializers\"","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711126,"modifiedTime":1674268711126,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"HJAxlXGPhHmPF8lm","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mind Link","type":"power","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/moulinette/tiles/custom/icons-custom/feats/feats/improved-feint.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.gGR22ulOuzp3h7n7"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Mind link </em>creates a telepathic connection between two individuals (which does not necessarily have to include the caster). The link accommodates only willing subjects and communication&mdash;thoughts that aren't consciously transmitted aren't relayed.</p>\n<p>Once @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{activated}, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} between all linked minds is one mile, or five with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p>If any of the linked characters suffers a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, all others must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} roll or be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} (this cannot cause a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}).</p>\n<p>The speed of communication is that of normal speech, but with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} members may communicate up to 30 seconds or so of speech on a single combat turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Broadcast (+2): </span>The caster can broadcast a short telepathic message to every sentient mind within @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} &times;4 radius (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} &times;8 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}). The caster can only broadcast, she doesn't receive their responses.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Long Distance Link (+3): </span>Casters can connect with any mind they're familiar with on the same plane of existence, regardless of distance.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"30 minutes","trapping":"Headpieces, talismans, of Tao or other gods, crystals","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711143,"modifiedTime":1674268711143,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"JNOc7IAuvU9NuDjr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Slumber","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/control/sleep-bubble-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.19Mvc7O3XQNpsrPm"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Those who favor stealth or want to avoid harming their foes are drawn to this spell, which puts its victims into a deep and restful sleep.</p>\n<p>Anyone affected by <em>slumber </em>must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll (at &minus;2 if the caster got a raise on her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll). Those who fail fall asleep for the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Duration]{Duration} of the spell. Very loud noises or attempts to physically wake a sleeper (by shaking him, for example), grant another @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+2/+3): </span>For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"A lullaby, blowing powder or sand at targets","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711294,"modifiedTime":1674268711294,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"JWOHH4k0G3r4S2X2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
