{"name":"Repair","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/trades/smithing-anvil-silver-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.3mvXRje8icgL0ajL"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Repair</em> fixes damage to objects, such as weapons, equipment, or furnishing. The DM must first determine if the object is already destroyed. If so, no <em>repair </em>may be attempted. If not, a successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll repairs the construct or object. This can physically repair a magic item but can not restore magic to such an item. If the casting fails another attempt can be made an hour later. On a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, the damage can only be repaired through normal hard work and replacement parts.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Repairing (Special):</span>&nbsp;<em>Repairing&nbsp;</em>allows an artificer to repair damage done to complex machines and objects that is not entirely destroyed&mdash;essentially any device that has @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} like constructs or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Vehicles]{vehicles}. For 2 additional Power Points certain types of constructs and living constructs can be affected. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Vehicles]{Vehicles} cost an additional 4 Power Points plus or minus 1 for each size Scale difference from Normal. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} repairs one Wound, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} repairs two. If the casting fails or does not heal all the damage, the artificer may try again after a rest. On a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, the damage can only be repaired through normal hard work and replacement parts.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Repairing (+10):</span> <em>Greater repairing</em> can actually rebuild objects that are completely broken as long as all parts are still available. This spell may also be used to restore constructs (but not living constructs) that have perished.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Mass Repair (+2/+3): </span>For a +2 Power Points, repair affects all allies within a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster (or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +3).</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Repair Crippling Injuries (+15): </span>For Living Constructs, the power can repair a permanent @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation} in the Savage Worlds core rules). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it fails, this caster cannot heal that particular injury (but someone else may try). If successful, the subject is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} for 24 hours.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Laying on of hands, working on object with a toolset.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711160,"modifiedTime":1674268711160,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"OCufBdFxssFjlG8q","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Time Stop","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/time/clock-spinning-gold-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y6l3qfj0w3","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.DVGkec6BAkNEUtFg"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Time is a constant for most, but not this chronomancer. The spell slows time for all but the caster, granting her a new turn immediately after she finishes this one. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, she gets up to four actions on the turn instead of three and can ignore up to 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalties. Time stop can only be cast once per round.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"8","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A glowing hourglass, floating ice particles, blurring.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268710999,"modifiedTime":1674268710999,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"OQNwG8oyOYksAnbN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Message","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/birds/corvid-call-sound-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.bEdGbmQSI2wVfodF"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Message </em>can allow the wizard to deliver a message of up to twenty-five words, or fifty words with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, to a creature in which the wizard is familiar with. The recipient recognizes the sender if it knowns them, and can answer the message in a like manner.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">More Words (+1/+2): </span>The caster can increase the number of words within the message doubling them from 1 Power Points or quadrupling them for 2 Power Points.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Sending (+2): </span>For 2 Power Points the message can be sent across any distance and even to other planes of existance.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Unknown Recipient (+2): </span>For 2 Power Points the caster can send a message to a recipient that he is not familiar with provided the caster knows something that can identify the recipient.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2 miles","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Whispered message to an animal, message delivered on the wind.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711278,"modifiedTime":1674268711278,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"OyywhbnaZ1GlZCWL","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Mark","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.dLePOjvRVQHt7Df6"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The caster creates a small unique&nbsp;<em>arcane mark</em> on a surface that cannot be removed expect by a&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.N0LX7ogCmpSL81t7]{dispel}</em> at &ndash;2. The&nbsp;<em>mark</em> can be visible or invisible. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.y0R2MxxUXo1YhhVf]{Detect Arcana}</em> will reveal an&nbsp;<em>arcane mark.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Illusory Script (+2): </span>Instead of a mark, the caster writes a message. Any creature designated when the power is cast can read the message as normal script. To all others, the writing appears to be an unintelligible script or an entirely different message.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Suggestion (+3):</span> <em>Illusory script only.</em> The caster can designate specific individuals who can read it automatically. To everyone else it appears as described above, but with an added effect of a non-harmful suggestion such as \"This scroll never existed.\" The suggestion must be defined when the power is activated. When the suggestion is triggered, the unauthorized reader must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll originally made to activate the power.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Arcane runes, enchanted paper, magically transcribed spoken words.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711033,"modifiedTime":1674268711033,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"PnB8Rl8dgcgRbRD3","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Sound/Silence","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/sonic/scream-wail-shout-teal.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.9ViwFVILmCFermGz"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Sound </em>mimics any known sound or voice, emanating from a point of origin within @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} at a volume up to the sound of a loud shout. If used as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}, the defender @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposes} the casting roll with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts}.</p>\n<p><em>Silence </em>does the opposite, muting all sound up to a loud shout within a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. This subtracts 4 from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls made by those inside the area of effect, as well as anyone trying to hear sounds made from within. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} completely mutes all sound inside the template&mdash;such @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls automatically fail.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">ALARM (+1/+2):</span> <em>Sound</em> only. Alarm creates a subtle ward on an area you select. Once the spell effect is in place, it thereafter sounds an alarm each time a creature enters the warded area or touches it. A being who speaks the password (determined at the time of casting) doesn't set off the alarm.<br />The warning lasts 10 hours. It costs one Power Point to ward an object and two Power Points to ward an area 5\" (10 yards) in diameter. <br />The spellcaster can choose for the alarm to be audible only to him (this must be chosen when cast).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">BELLOW (+1):</span> <em>Sound </em>only. The character&rsquo;s voice booms out, carrying over one mile distant&mdash;a useful way of warning populations of impending danger. Doing so also adds +2 to one Intimidation Test as long any subjects are within 12&rdquo; (24 yards).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Sound/Silence (+1): </span>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} roll made to resist a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} (or Targeted modifier) is made at &minus;2.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mobile (+1): </span>The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{round}.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Targeted (+0): </span>Instead of casting <em>silence </em>in an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area of effect}, the caster may instead target individuals in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range} for 1 Power Point each. Unwilling targets resist with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} (at &minus;2 if the caster gets a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts ×5 (sound); Smarts (silence)","duration":"Instant (sound); 5 (silence)","trapping":"Magical effects, a brief ripple in the air, a bell or chime that starts or stops ringing","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711179,"modifiedTime":1674268711179,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"RJQJvtqtbds9dUpC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Boost/Lower Trait","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/melee/unarmed-punch-fist.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Aii4dhYLbc4Xf8mf"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This power allows a character to increase or decrease a target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (attribute or skill).</p>\n<p><em>Boosting </em>an ally's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} increases the selected Trait one die type, or two with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, for five rounds.</p>\n<p><em>Lowering </em>an enemy's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} has a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Duration]{Duration} of Instant and lowers the selected attribute or skill a die type with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, or two with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} (to a minimum of d4). A victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns. Success improves the effect one die type, and a raise removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p>Additional castings don't stack on a single @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (take the highest), but may affect different Traits.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Boost/Lower Trait (+2): </span>With success, the selected @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Trait} gains a free reroll once per round, or once per action with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. For <em>lower Trait</em> the target applies a &minus;2 penalty to the affected Trait's rolls.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Strong (+1): </span><em>Lower Trait</em> only. The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5 (boost); Instant (lower)","trapping":"Physical change, glowing aura, potions","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711057,"modifiedTime":1674268711057,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"RdJm4yfZaePP1GMW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Damage Field","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/sonic/explosion-impact-shock-wave.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.FC8ifOJDwA3wPPGN"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Damage field</em> creates a dangerous aura around the recipient that harms foes foolish enough to get too close.</p>\n<p>At the end of the affected character's turn, all adjacent beings (including allies!) automatically take 2d4 damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+2): </span>The caster may extend the <em>damage field</em> into a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} centered on herself, the caster is immune to her own damage field.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Damage (+2): </span>The damage field causes 2d6 damage.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Damage Field (+4): </span>The <em>damage field</em> causes 3d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage}.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Mobile (+2): </span>Mobile works only with the Area of Effect modifier. It allows the caster to detach the <em>damage field</em> from himself and move it up to his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} die type each round as a limited free action.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"4","damage":"2d4","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Fiery aura, spikes, electrical field","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711247,"modifiedTime":1674268711247,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"RkyLQqCKPALiTssP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Intangibility","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/unholy/hand-fire-skeleton-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.4HTUERx7eSf1JP4g"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>With a successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll, whoever receives this power becomes incorporeal. He is unable to affect the physical world, and it cannot affect him. He can travel through walls, and non-magical weapons pass straight through him. Any items carried at the time of casting are also incorporeal.</p>\n<p>While incorporeal, the character may affect other incorporeal beings (including himself), and he is still susceptible to supernatural attacks, including powers and enchanted items. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} on the activation roll, reduce the damage from supernatural attacks by 4.</p>\n<p>The being becomes corporeal when the power ends, but if within someone or something he's shunted to the nearest open space and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{stunned}.</p>\n<p>If cast on an unwilling target, the victim resists with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}. If affected, he shakes off the effect with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll as a free action at the end of his following turns.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+2): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 2 additional Power Points each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+3): </span>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Ghost form, body of shadow, gaseous transformation","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711340,"modifiedTime":1674268711340,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"SOtjTN1l8fQfcwi3","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Teleport","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/water/projectile-ice-impact-stone.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.FxYVkbm30Nf2OSxE"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Teleport allows a character to disappear and instantly reappear up to 12&Prime; (24 yards) distant, or double that with a raise. Teleporting to an unseen location incurs a &minus;2 penalty on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p>Opponents adjacent to a character who teleports away don't get a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack} (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{Withdrawing From Melee}).</p>\n<p>If casting teleport on willing subjects, the caster decides where they move to, not the targets.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Teleport (+5): </span>With concentration, the character can teleport much farther. The caster must concentrate on her destination for at least one round, taking no other actions. This makes her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}; if @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}, the spell fails.\n<p>For one round of concentration, the character can teleport up to 100 miles. For two rounds, she can travel 1000 miles, and with three rounds, she can go anywhere on Eberron. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} transports the recipient to a random location (DM's call) on the same plane of existence.</p>\n<p>If you've physically been there yourself, there is no modifier to your roll. With success you arrive within 2d6 x 10 feet of your target, or on target with a raise.</p>\n<p>If you have a detailed map or have seen it through a power or device, you suffer a &ndash;2 to the roll. With success you arrive within 2d6 x 100 feet, or on target with a raise.</p>\n<p>If you have a crude map or a general notion of the place on a regional or world map, you suffer a &ndash;4. You arrive within 2d10 miles with success, or within 2d6 x 100 feet with a raise.</p>\n<p>In the absence of such information, teleporting is not possible.</p>\n<p>A Critical Failure transports the recipient to a random location (DM's call) on the same plane of existence.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Gate (+5): </span>Instead of teleporting, the caster opens a temporary portal connecting her current location and the destination. Creatures and objects can travel through this gate from either side for the Duration of the power.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Teleport Foe (+2): </span>Foes may be targeted by a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Touch Attack]{Touch attack}. This is an action, which must be the second part of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} if the attack is successful. The foe resists the casting with an opposed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll against the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} total and is sent up to 12&Prime; away with success and 24&Prime; with a raise. Foes may not be teleported into solid objects.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A cloud of smoke, “phasing” out, change into a bolt of lightning.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711300,"modifiedTime":1674268711300,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"TS8nEIYw79AbLO4B","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Puppet","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/control/control-influence-puppet.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.JD9spUOc5xOQLuqa"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Puppet </em>is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of the character's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} versus the target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}. With @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, the victim automatically obeys commands that don't directly harm himself or those he cares about.</p>\n<p>With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the target is completely controlled, but gets an automatic @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} to avoid directly harming himself or those he cares about. If the <em>puppet</em>'s resistance @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{succeeds}, he doesn't carry out that particular command but doesn't otherwise resist his master. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, he breaks the controller's hold and the power ends.</p>\n<p>Commands are general, such as &ldquo;attack that person&rdquo; or &ldquo;open that door.&rdquo; The controller doesn't get to dictate how many @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{actions} the victim uses in a turn, whether or not he uses his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sweep]{Sweep} Edge, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+2): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 2 additional Power Points each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Strong (+2): </span>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} rolls to resist commands are made at &minus;2. If the caster uses <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{mind link}</em> on the target, she may extend her control of him to any distance, even out of her sight.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Glowing eyes, trance-like state, a swinging pocket watch, voodoo dolls.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711355,"modifiedTime":1674268711355,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"TpoRRHModi8fe8mw","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Summon Monster","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/fire/elemental-fire-flying.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.9RXoXcRzUIWJN4B3"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Conjuring a mindless ally or simple beast is one thing. But summoning a monster is a true display of a sorcerer&rsquo;s power!</p>\n<p>Summoned monsters are loyal to the caster, understand simple commands, and act on the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.b0BBoKY0d5GZgOVk]{Action Card}.</p>\n<p>Monsters return to from whence they came when the spell expires.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Monsters (Varies): </span>Additional allies of the same type may be summoned at the same time for half the Power Point cost of the original summons (total cost including modifiers, rounded up).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+1): </span><em>Summon monster's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Increased Trait (+1): </span>The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 Power Point. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mind Rider (+1): </span>The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Summon Animal</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Monster</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Basilisk</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Basilisk, Great</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">V</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Brownie</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Burrower</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">7</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Chimera</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Cockatrice</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Cockatrice</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Crocotta</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Darkmantle</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Dragon, Young</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">V</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">11</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Elemental (Small)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Elemental</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Fire Salamander</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Gargoyle</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Griffin</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Hippogriff</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Khazok</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Manticore</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Minotaur</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Owlbear</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Peryton</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Rust Monster</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Wyvern</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Clay figure that grows into a servant, a tattoo that comes to life.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711202,"modifiedTime":1674268711202,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"UIabn5crJiOlr5Hk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Stun","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/water/projectiles-ice-explosion.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.PDWUggLVmStYS6kr"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Stun </em>shocks a target with concussive force, sound, light, magical energy, or the like.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} casting means the victim must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} roll (at &minus;2 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll) or be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+2/+3): </span>For +2 Power Points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Bolts of energy, stun bombs, sonic booms, burst of blinding light","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711186,"modifiedTime":1674268711186,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"VcMIMnBesY2xuwc1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Burrow","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/earth/barrier-stone-explosion-debris.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.nAJNHUyTqyDqCwO1"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Burrow</em> allows the recipient to meld into raw earth. He can remain underground if he wants in a sort of \"limbo\" or <em>burrow</em> through the ground at half his normal @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} (or full Pace with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}). He may not run. </p>\n<p>A <em>burrowing </em>character may attempt to suprise a foe by making an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} versus @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll. If the burrower wins, the target is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to <em>him only</em>. With a raise, the burrower gets @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}. Targets on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hold]{Hold} may attempt to interrupt the attack before it occurs.</p>\n<p>Burrowers can't usually @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Surprise]{surprise} a foe once their presence is known, but can still burrow for protection and mobility. </p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+1): </span>The caster can <em>burrow</em> through stone, concrete, or similar substances. (Some substances, like plastic, glass, solid lead, etc., might be resistant at the DM's discreation.)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Dissolving into the earth and appearing elsewhere.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711062,"modifiedTime":1674268711062,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Z7ar9lgkRIbK5jmG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Drain Power Points","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_aezbjjp7ce","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.xzLINR13ZmeVNWOz"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Powerful mages, priests, and other arcanists can use this ability to drain magical energy from their foes. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} they can even leech the stolen energy for themselves.</p>\n<p>The power is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}, and the caster suffers a &minus;2 penalty to her roll if the target has a different Arcane Background than her own.</p>\n<p>Success drains 1d6 of the rival's Power Points (if any, and the die doesn't Ace). With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the caster adds the points to her own. This may take her above her usual maximum! They last until used, and must be the first spent when casting.</p>\n<p><em>Drain Power Points</em> can also be used on an arcane device (the creator still resists with her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} whether she wields it or not). The device can't lose more Power Points than it has.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+2): </span>The caster drains 2d6 Power Points with success..</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Gusty winds, wings, broomsticks","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711331,"modifiedTime":1674268711331,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ZBQhQzzj1butGX86","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Detect/Conceal Arcana","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/melee/weapons-crossed-swords-teal.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.y0R2MxxUXo1YhhVf"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Detect arcana </em>allows the recipient of the power to see and detect all supernatural persons, objects, or effects in sight for five rounds. This includes <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisible}</em> foes, enchantments on people or items, weird science devices, and so on. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the caster knows the type of enchantment as well.</p>\n<p>When used on a supernatural creature, the caster learns its active powers and arcane abilities. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, he knows @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weaknesses} common to that creature type. This doesn't reveal @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weaknesses} of unique individuals, if any. Those must usually be discovered through research or trial and error.</p>\n<p><strong>Invisible Creatures:</strong> <em>Detect arcana </em>also allows a character to ignore up to 4 points of penalties when attacking foes hidden by magical darkness, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}, or similar abilities (or all penalties with a raise).</p>\n<p><em>Conceal arcana</em> obscures one being or item of Normal Scale or smaller from the detect magic ability for one hour (see Detect Magic on page 169 and the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size Table]{Size Table}). For larger creatures, increase the cost based on the Scale Modifier (+2 PPs for Large, +4 PPs for Huge, or +6 PPs for Gargantuan).</p>\n<p>With a success, attempts to <em>detect arcana</em> on the being or item suffer a &ndash;2 penalty or &ndash;4 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. If <em>detect arcana</em> fails, the character cannot see through the ruse with this casting and is not aware it is concealed unless presented with obvious evidence of such (for example, the attack of an invisible foe).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one viewer for <em>detect</em>, or item for <em>conceal</em>, for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Alignment Sense (+1): </span>The caster can sense the presence and exact location of supernatural good or evil within range. <em>Detect arcana</em> activated with Alignment Sense no longer requires line of sight to locate creatures.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+1/+2): </span><em>Conceal </em>only. The power affects everything in a sphere the size of a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} for +1 points, or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +2.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Identify (+1): </span>The caster can identify a magic item's powers and how they work.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Strong (+1): </span><em>Conceal </em>only. <em>Detection </em>rolls to see through the <em>concealment </em>are made at &minus;2. This stacks with the additional penalty for casting with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5 (detect); one hour (conceal)","trapping":"Waving hands, whispered words.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711090,"modifiedTime":1674268711090,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ZFFSDYrdFYbKeMah","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Barrier","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/lightning/barrier-shield-crackling-orb-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.tdRvBUp3vBVmwjBC"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Barrier </em>creates a straight wall 5&Prime; (10 yards) long and 1&Prime; (two yards) tall, of immobile material that conforms to the surface it's cast upon. Double the length with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p>Thickness varies depending on what the wall is made of, but is usually a few inches.</p>\n<p>The wall is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 8, and may be destroyed as any other object (see @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Breaking Things]{Breaking Things}). Each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} destroys a 1\" (2 yard) square section of wall (piercing weapons can't damage the barrier).</p>\n<p>When the spell expires or the wall is broken it crumbles to dust or dissipates. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trappings} are never left behind.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Bridge (+1): </span>The <em>barrier </em>can be shaped to be flat and act as a bridge or roof.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Damage (+1): </span>The <em>barrier </em>causes 2d4 damage to anyone who contacts it.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Deadly (+2): </span>The <em>barrier </em>causes 2d6 damage.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Tough (+1): </span>The wall is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 10.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Shaped (+1): </span>The <em>barrier </em>forms a circle, square, or rectangle. It can't have a roof or floor, and can't Bind or Entangle anything within (use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle} power for that).</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Size (+1): </span>The length and height of the <em>barrier </em>doubles.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Fire, ice, thorns, force, bones, energy.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711223,"modifiedTime":1674268711223,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ZkUfmGOP9Gq6Z4TF","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Empathy","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.opeQkJyOGyPeEat4"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A successful @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} vs @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll gives the caster insight into a target's basic emotions. This grants him a +1 bonus (+2 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) to all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception},@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} rolls against the target for the Duration of the power.</p>\n<p><em>Empathy</em> works on animals, adding +1 (+2 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) to@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Animal Handling]{Animal Handling}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding} or other rolls to interact with the creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Charm (+2): </span>If the target is Uncooperative or Neutral, a successful casting makes him Cooperative, or Friendly with a raise. The spell is instantly broken if the caster or her allies attack the victim or her allies.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+1): </span>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds. If the character Critically Fails any of the affected skill rolls against the target, the effect terminates immediately.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Truth (+2): </span>The caster knows if the target believes he's telling the truth or not.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration, a warm or sympathetic smile, exchanging a pleasantry","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711101,"modifiedTime":1674268711101,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ZszaXnnZlyJLvkT5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Resurrection","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/holy/chalice-glowing-gold-water.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y6l3qfj0w3","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Kp7NJn5xdhobUC7c"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Perhaps the greatest power of all is the ability to bring someone back from the dead. It can restore lost loves, bring solace to the grieving, and topple kingdoms.</p>\n<p>Returning the dead to life requires a reasonably complete corpse no more than a year old. The caster then prays, meditates, chants, or otherwise concentrates on mending the body and pulling the spirit back to it for four hours.</p>\n<p>Once done, the healer makes a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{casting roll} at &minus;4. If successful, the victim returns to life with three @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted}. With a raise, she returns merely @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Resurrection (+10):</span>The boundaries of life and death no longer matter. A caster can restore the dead to life regardless of how long the target was dead and even without a corpse. To resurrect the dead in this fashion requires a twelve-hour ritual and leaves the caster Exhausted.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+5):</span> The hero can raise a spirit dead up to a decade for +5 Power Points.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"20","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Elaborate ceremonies, rare plants, magical amulets, divine intervention","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268710995,"modifiedTime":1674268710995,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"aRumBWgybWwDmjdn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Deflection","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-deflect-gold.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sb5DePEKWohVXVmg"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Deflection </em>powers work in a variety of ways. Some manifestations actually deflect incoming @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{attacks}, others blur the target's form or produce illusionary effects. The end result is always the same, however&mdash;to misdirect incoming melee and missile @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{attacks} from the recipient of the power.</p>\n<p>With success, foes must subtract 2 from either melee or ranged attacks (caster's choice). With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the penalty applies to both.</p>\n<p>An attacker who uses a ranged weapon in melee against the recipient suffers the penalty either way.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Mystical shield, gust of wind, phantom servant that intercepts missiles","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711083,"modifiedTime":1674268711083,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"bwvq96E6JMKqgje3","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Elemental Manipulation","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/symbols/elements-air-earth-fire-water.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.9uh5ogySlRjqMFPr"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This power grants basic control over the four traditional elements: air, earth, fire, and water (the elements may vary for other cultures). Upon activation, the caster may choose one of the following effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">ATTACK:</span> The caster uses their activation roll as an attack roll, dealing 2d4 damage to a target (3d4 with a raise) within Range.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">MOVE:</span> The caster may move a cubic foot of air, earth (half that in stone), fire, or water up to the caster&rsquo;s Smarts in any direction as a limited action.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">PUSH:</span> The elements to buffet and move the target. The caster uses his activation roll in place of his Strength for a Push.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">SPECIAL EFFECTS:</span> The caster may use the elements to create an additional effect with the GM&rsquo;s approval. Some examples are using air to blow out a torch, fan a flame, or cool someone down (reroll a Fatigue roll in oppressive heat). The caster may use earth to cover tracks, fix breaks in stone or earthen walls, or use fire to conjure flame about the size of a torch or spread existing flame (see Fire). He may use water to conjure a quart of water (not &ldquo;inside&rdquo; objects or people) or purify a gallon of water per casting.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After activation, each additional use of the effects above are an action. Roll a new arcane skill roll for Attack or Push (these rolls do not suffer Backlash for Critical Failures as they are not activation rolls).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+2): </span>The volume of air, earth, fire, or water affected is tripled and increases the Strength a die type (air or water) or base damage to 2d6 (earth, fire).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Weather (+8): </span>The caster can summon or dispel storms, bring a cooling rain, scorch the earth with a heatwave, or even bring snow to the hottest climes.\n<p>The caster can bring or disperse rain, snow, sun, and wind in about a five-mile radius. The severity depends on the local environment&mdash;a harsh desert might receive gentle rain while a rain forest gets a driving downpour. The effects take 10 minutes to create and lasts an hour.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"A few simple gestures","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Savage Pathfinder"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711097,"modifiedTime":1674268711097,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"da03xzaxeG5QtVrC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Conjure Item","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/nature/cornucopia-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.2YhwQ0DX3HNIVpxG"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The caster can create an object weighing up to one pound for every 2 Power Points spent. The item must be a simple, mundane object made of a common material (DM's call) such as a 10-foot pole, blanket, shield, etc. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll produces an more durable version of the conjured item.</p>\n<p>Conjured items appear in the hands of the caster or on the ground nearby. Once the Duration expires, the item fades from reality. This can cause issues, for example, if the conjured item holds a door open or was given as a gift.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Complexity (+2): </span>The item conjured can have modest artistry and modest complex moving parts.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Complete (+1): </span>The object is a complete set, such as a chess set or a quiver of arrows. The set must fit under the weight limit.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Create Food and Water (Special): </span>Instead of an object, every 1 Power Point creates enough food and water to sustain a Size 0 humanoid for one day. The nourishing food is permanent (doesn't disappear after you eat it), although it decays and becomes inedible after 24 hours if not consumed. The water is just like clean rainwater and does not spoil.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Creation (+4): </span>For +4 Power Points, the object created can have the volume of 1 cubic foot per 2 Power Points spent rather than one pound.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Durable (+1 per pound): </span>The object's Duration becomes &ldquo;permanent&rdquo; until dispelled. The Power Points are &ldquo;invested&rdquo; and unavailable until it's destroyed, dispelled, or dismissed by the caster. The conjurer may dismiss the object at any time, regardless of sight, distance, or other factors. His Power Points then begin recharging normally.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Light that forms the item’s silhouette, reaching into a magic bag, shaping dirt or clay into the item, pulling the item from a drawing or painting.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711075,"modifiedTime":1674268711075,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"dfVppwHf4dk5lg7R","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Summon Undead","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/death/undead-skeleton-fire-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.IUYu8TFx6wAlBU0t"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.DTbVXVhrP959vdV3]{Zombie} power raises basic undead that serve a necromancer&rsquo;s whims for an hour. Summon undead doesn&rsquo;t require existing corpses but brings them from wherever they currently haunt to the necromancer&rsquo;s current location. They serve for a limited time, but are much more powerful than those typically summoned in groaning hordes of walking dead or clinking mobs of chattering skeletons.</p>\n<p>Summoned undead appear as listed in the Bestiary of this book or Savage Worlds, including any equipment in their profile.</p>\n<p>When the power expires, the loathsome dead fade back through shadow to their original location.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Undead (Varies): </span>Additional allies of the same type may be summoned at the same time for half the Power Point cost of the original summons (total cost including modifiers, rounded up).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+1): </span><em>Summon monster's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Increased Trait (+1): </span>The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 Power Point. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mind Rider (+1): </span>The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Summon Animal</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Monster</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Ghost</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Ghost Blade</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Ghoul</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Grave Guardian</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Guardian Mummy</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Shadow</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Skelton, Flaming</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Skeleton, Motley</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Skeleton, Giant</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Wight</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">7</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Zombie</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">3</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Animal bones or feathers of appropriate sort, glyphs, chanting.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711206,"modifiedTime":1674268711206,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"eKLs9q7Ojh1oZkXd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Lock/Unlock","type":"power","img":"icons/sundries/misc/lock-steel-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.4Y6vWKSXhpV6Am3H"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Lock</em> magically seals a door, window, container, envelope, drawer, box, or other closeable item. Any attempt to open it is increased by &ndash;4, or &ndash;8 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.gl7I9tF6bDt1r0c9]{raise}. The caster may set a pass phrase when the lock is created; the portal opens for anyone who speaks the phrase and remains open until the phrase is repeated.</p>\n<p>Conversely, <em>unlock</em> opens sealed objects, ignoring up to 4 points of penalties from mechanical locks or the <em>lock</em> spell, or 8 points with a raise.</p>\n<p>Neither spell has any effect on barriers, barricades, or blockages&mdash;only distinct objects which can be opened or shut.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Special (lock); Instant (Unlock)","trapping":"Whispered words, scattering dust on a door, aura around lock, tapping a lock three times.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711275,"modifiedTime":1674268711275,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"fAAc8NHKYjI7Z4DR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mind Reading","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/perception/third-eye-blue-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.zyIbjqyk1nMXrSHm"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Mind reading </em>is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} versus the target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts}. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} allows the character to gain one truthful answer from the subject. The target is aware of the mental intrusion unless the mind reader gets a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. The DM may apply @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{modifiers} based on the subject's mental @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Hindrances]{Hindrances} or current state of mind.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Mind Walk (+2): </span>The caster has greater access to the target's mind and memories, unlocking an entire scene or chain of related memories (DM's call).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Psionic invasion, soulsight","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711147,"modifiedTime":1674268711147,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"fTCQJmlCwsR38mvg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Sanctuary","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/symbols/star-rising-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.cNNVPH3ZikrS8Qy5"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Any evil creature attempting a damaging attack that targets or affects the recipient must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll (at &minus;2 if cast with a raise). If the roll fails, the creature loses that action.</p>\n<p>If the caster (or any allies affected by the Area Effect modifier) attempt to harm anyone (evil or otherwise), <em>sanctuary </em>terminates instantly.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+2/+3): </span>For +2 Power Points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Consecrate Ground (+8): </span>An area roughly 30 yards quare becomes anathema to forces of darkness (or light). At the start of each round the creature attempts to enter in the sacred ground they must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll (at &minus;2 if cast with a raise) or suffer a level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.tGBCnKkDi55VRxgm]{Fatigue}.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Strong (+1): </span>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} rolls by the creature are made at &minus;2 (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Words of power, holy symbol, glowing light","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711165,"modifiedTime":1674268711165,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"fx85aWwHK3hJoByJ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Champion of Faith","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/melee/sword-winged-holy-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.aRGWYRT5QATvSIhJ"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Champion of Faith allows the caster to grant divine favor. For the duration of the spell, the recipient gains the benefits of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Champion]{Champion} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Holy/Unholy Warrior} Edge, chosen at the time of casting. Both edges can be taken on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Holy Aura","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711238,"modifiedTime":1674268711238,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"gFUR4kXPxYQvHsL1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Locate","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-luck-fortune-gold.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.BXGsr52kZZMNhlpf"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Often it's almost, if not literally, impossible to find something via mundane means. Locate allows the caster to find these hidden things.</p>\n<p>When casters use this power, they choose an object, creature, or location. If the caster has never seen the target, the roll is at &minus;2. A success gives a sense of the general direction and distance of the target. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} also gives an impression of the target (e.g., the creature is asleep, the object is in a strongbox, the secret door is behind a bookshelf).</p>\n<p><strong>Running Water:</strong> On Eberron, running water blocks <em>locate</em> if it's in the path between the caster and the target.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Find the Path (+1): </span>In addition to the direction and distance to a person, place, or thing, the caster also has a supernatural sense of the best or fastest way to navigate to the target's general area.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"A floating crystal over a map, message in the clouds, a ray of light.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711139,"modifiedTime":1674268711139,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"gXQh6VRU46K8aWre","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Dispel","type":"power","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/moulinette/tiles/custom/icons-custom/feats/feats/combat-casting.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.N0LX7ogCmpSL81t7"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Dispel </em>allows a hero to negate enemy powers. It has no effect on permanent enchantments or innate abilities such as a dragon's breath or a banshee's scream. <em>Dispel </em>affects @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Arcane Devices]{arcane devices} normally.</p>\n<p><em>Dispel </em>can be used on a power already in effect or to counter an enemy power as it's being used. The latter requires the countering mage to be on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hold]{Hold} and interrupt his foe's action.</p>\n<p>In either case, <em>dispelling </em>an opponent's power is an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of arcane skills (with a &minus;2 modifier if the rival's power is of another type such as magic vs. miracles, psionics vs. weird science, etc.).</p>\n<p>If the <em>dispelling </em>character wins, the targeted power ends immediately (or fails if it was countered with the usual results of failure). With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the recipient of the <em>dispelled </em>power is also @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Anti-magic Field (+4): </span>Instead of affecting a power at Range, this modifier creates a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster with a Duration of 5. Magic items, effects, and powers have no effect within the field. Summoned creatures that enter the field must make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll each round or take a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}. Anti-Magic Field can't be combined with any other modifiers.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area Effect (+2/+4/+6): </span>The effect covers an area: +2 Power Points uses a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template}, +4 Power Points uses @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium}, or +6 Power Points uses @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large}. The caster makes one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll, then each affected target makes an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll to oppose it. This affects all powers in the target area unless the caster also uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Selective]{Selective} Power Modifier.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Disenchant (+1): </span>The caster can target a magical item rather than an individual or a power. This is a standard @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll, not an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll}, at &minus;2 penalty (&minus;4 for artifacts, DM's call). If successful, all the item's magical abilities are negated for one round, or two with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Multiple Powers (+1): </span>If successful, the caster <em>dispels</em> all the target's currently activated powers.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">REMOVE CURSE (+2):</span> This ignores the &ndash;2 penalty when attempting to end the curse power. Additionally, it can be used to end the effect of cursed items.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Waving hands, whispered words","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711093,"modifiedTime":1674268711093,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"h5ZTtFF9iRVyLqHa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Protection","type":"power","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/moulinette/tiles/custom/icons-custom/spells/runes/protect-sky-2.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.z4JIPOi6zOwnl9z1"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with arcane protection means hostile powers suffer a &minus;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) to affect this character.</p>\n<p>If the power causes harm, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{damage} is also reduced a like amount. Arcane Protection stacks with @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} should the recipient have both!</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Arcane Protection (+2): </span>Hostile powers suffer a &minus;4 penalty (&minus;6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration, a dull glow around the protected character, a fetish","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711037,"modifiedTime":1674268711037,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"i7SSAhQ0IVe3dnDR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Fear","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/magical/spirit-fear-energy-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.2B3zBBJWGLOuRs8y"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This power causes overwhelming dread and horror. The target makes a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} roll. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} who fail are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Panicked} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}. If the power is cast with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the Fear roll is at &minus;2 and Wild Cards add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table} results.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+2/+3): </span>For +2 Power Points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Fear (+2): </span>Fear rolls are made at &minus;2, or &minus;4 if cast with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Gestures, eldritch energy, cold chills","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711114,"modifiedTime":1674268711114,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"iPEWv6mstW3plpbx","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Gift of Battle","type":"power","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.IOH9e51aVemYrERj"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Gift of battle </em>grants the target tactical insight and leadership qualities.</p>\n<p>With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll, the recipient gains the benefits of a single Leadership @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Edges]{Edge} chosen by the caster. The caster (not the recipient) must have the same @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank} or higher as the Edge's Requirements.</p>\n<p>With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the recipient gains two Leadership Edges. He need not meet any requirements except those of other Edges. For instance, the hero cannot gain @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fervor]{Fervor} unless he scores a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} and takes @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command]{Command} first, or already has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Command]{Command} Edge.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+4): </span>The recipient gains two (or three with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}) Leadership Edges at once.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"4","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Gestures, prayer, whispered words, concentration","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711263,"modifiedTime":1674268711263,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"igKE6HhqRP4HjLpF","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Sloth/Speed","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/movement/feet-winged-boots-brown.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.ldVHKdr9G926Rz0s"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Sloth </em>lessens celerity and coordination while <em>speed </em>increases it. It halves the target's total @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{movement} each @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{round} (round up). With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, movement is also an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{action}. The target automatically attempts to shake off the effects of <em>sloth </em>at the end of each of his next turns by making a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with <em>speed </em>doubles the target's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{movement} (basic Pace and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{running}). With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} the character also ignores the &minus;2 running penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+2/+3): </span><em>Sloth</em> only. For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Dash (+2): </span><em>Speed </em>only. The recipient's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{running die} isn't rolled&mdash;she gains the maximum result possible.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Quickness (+2): </span><em>Speed </em>only. The character's total @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty each turn is reduced by 2 (she can do two actions at no penalty, or three at &minus;2 each).</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Strong (+1): </span><em>Sloth</em> only. The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off <em>sloth's </em>effects is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant (sloth); 5 (speed)","trapping":"Slowing time, blurred motion, a slippery patch of oil or ice","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711290,"modifiedTime":1674268711290,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"iwhsfUJibdpljS0E","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Scrying","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-tendrils-web-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.5rGBZhNbgLLs69Tn"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Scrying</em> allows the caster to secretly spy on a distant target. Preparing the spell takes one uninterrupted minute while the caster focuses on a target item, creature, or location. This makes her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} and unable to take any other actions. If she's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} during this time, the spell fails.</p>\n<p>If the caster has never seen the target herself, she makes her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll at &minus;2. <em>Scrying</em> on a target in a different plane of existence also imposes a &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p><em>Scrying</em> is opposed by the subject's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}. If the target wins, he knows he's being spied on. If the caster wins, he can see and hear the target and the area around it but cannot move his perspective. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, he can shift perspective and follow the target at a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} 24.</p>\n<p>A <em>scrying </em>\"eye\" may be seen with detect arcana (but not detect magic). It may also be dispelled (at &ndash;2 if suspected but not revealed).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Group Sight (+1): </span>The caster may share her perception with allies within a Range of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} for the power's Duration.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Images on a reflected surface, glowing eyes, a crystal ball","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711286,"modifiedTime":1674268711286,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"j8s9gUoYWD9fj01l","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Environmental Protection","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/nature/barrier-shield-wood-vines.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.rq5U1rHesSTRJxbC"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Adventurers sometimes travel beneath the waves, through planes of fire, or other hazardous environments. This power protects them from crushing depths, scathing heat, intense cold, and even radiation.</p>\n<p>Environmental protection allows the target to breathe, speak, and move at his normal @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} in an otherwise fatal environment. It protects him from intense heat, cold, radiation, pressure, and lack of oxygen.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} increases the Duration to eight hours.</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Enviromental Resistance (+1): </span>The power now offers environmental resistance, reducing damage from one energy source (fire, cold, electricity, etc.) by 4 (6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}).</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">PLANAR ADAPTATION (+2):</span> This power protects the target from the devastating effects of different planes that would normally overwhelm this spell. The subject doesn't suffer the ill effects from other planes, such as the plane of fire or negative energy. The duration becomes 1 hour.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"A mark on the forehead, potions, gills.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711110,"modifiedTime":1674268711110,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"jrEfUPP5kCOgKALt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Battle Song","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-notes-sound-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.bgDPGCSwVjYYQ14A"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This spell, beloved of warlike bards, skalds and dirgesingers, causes the targets to fly into a battle frenzy.</p>\n<p>Every creature within a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster, apart from the caster, is granted the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} Edge for the duration of the spell. On a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the targets immediately go berserk, as per the Edge. Unwilling recipients are allowed a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} to resist. This spell affects friends and foe alike.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+1): </span>For +1 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"5","trapping":"Poetry, battle chant.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711226,"modifiedTime":1674268711226,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"kf1O4venRtMuCThE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Farsight","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-slit-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.mwJrHdTGvCLVbrhu"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Farsight </em>allows the recipient to see in detail over great distances. She can read lips or read fine print up to a mile distant.</p>\n<p>With a raise, she also halves @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{range penalties} for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), or other abilities affected by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{Range}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Farsight (+2): </span>Allows the recipient to ignore all Range penalties, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} doubles sight range.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Invisibly marked targets, guiding winds, eagle eyes","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711259,"modifiedTime":1674268711259,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"m33DosLBD2jojMKg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Summon Ally","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/magical/construct-stone-earth-gray.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.9RXoXcRzUIWJN4B3"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This power allows the character to summon a magical servant from nothing. The ally typically takes the form of a basic humanoid of the appropriate Size but can appear differently based on the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.2 Trappings]{Trappings}. It materializes anywhere in Range, and with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll, it's @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Resilient]{Resilient} as well.</p>\n<p>The ally acts on its creator's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} and follows her commands to the best of its ability. It has no personality, creativity, or emotions. When the power ends or the ally is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, it fades into nothingness, leaving no trace behind.</p>\n<p>The type of servant that can be summoned depends on the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank}. With the DM's approval, the player may swap abilities. If a hero wants an attendant in the form of a wolf, for example, the caster might exchange the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} skill for @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival} so that the &ldquo;animal&rdquo; can track its foes.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Summon Ally</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Servant</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Novice</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Attendant</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Seasoned</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Bodyguard</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Veteran</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Mirror Self *</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Heroic</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">7</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Sentinel</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*<em>Mirror Self incurs a &minus;1 Casting Modifier per Rank above Veteran to a maximum of &minus;6 at Legendary</em></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Allies (Varies): </span>Additional allies of the same type may be summoned at the same time for half the Power Point cost of the original summons (total cost including modifiers, rounded up).</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Combat Edge (+1): </span>The ally has a Combat Edge (it must meet the Requirements as usual). You may take this modifier up to three times per ally.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+1): </span><em>Summon ally's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Flight (+2): </span>The ally can fly at @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{Pace} 12</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Increased Trait (+1): </span>The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 Power Point. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mind Rider (+1): </span>The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\n<h2>STATBLOCKS</h2>\n<p><strong>Attendant</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Attributes: </strong>Agility d4, Smarts d4, Spirit d4, Strength d4, Vigor d4<br /><strong>Skills:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>4; <strong>Parry: </strong>4; <strong>Toughness: </strong>4<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Claw: </strong>Str+d4.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.ZxhDcqeaeczy6VVM]{Construct}: </strong>+2 to recover from being @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}; ignore 1 point of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}; doesn't breathe, immune to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Disease]{disease}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.SvX4iRZWqRW9w5jX]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Bodyguard</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Attributes: </strong>Agility d6, Smarts d4, Spirit d6, Strength d6, Vigor d6<br /><strong>Skills: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d4, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d4<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>6; <strong>Parry: </strong>5; <strong>Toughness: </strong>7 (2)<br /><strong>Edges: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}<br /><strong>Gear: </strong>Melee attack (Str+d6).<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Armor +2: </strong>Hardened skin.</li>\n<li><strong><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.ZxhDcqeaeczy6VVM]{Construct}:</strong> </strong>See Attendant.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.SvX4iRZWqRW9w5jX]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Mirror Self<br /></strong>The ally is a clone of the caster except: it's an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}; it has the same number of current Power Points as the caster after subtracting for this casting; it cannot use the <em>summon ally </em>power; its @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{skills} (but not @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{attributes}) are one die type less (minimum d4) than the original; it has identical mundane equipment (no magical qualities, disappears when the power expires); has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.ZxhDcqeaeczy6VVM]{Construct} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.SvX4iRZWqRW9w5jX]{Fearless} abilities.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Sentinel<br />Attributes: </strong>Agility d6, Smarts d6, Spirit d8, Strength d12+2, Vigor d10<br /><strong>Skills: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d10, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d10, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} d8<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>6; <strong>Parry: </strong>7; <strong>Toughness: </strong>13 (4)<br /><strong>Edges: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sweep]{Sweep (Improved)}.<br /><strong>Gear: </strong>Melee attack (Str+d8).<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Armor +4: </strong>Stone skin.</li>\n<li><strong><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.ZxhDcqeaeczy6VVM]{Construct}:</strong> </strong>See Attendant.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.SvX4iRZWqRW9w5jX]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} 2: </strong>Sentinels are 8' tall and very dense.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Clay figure that grows into a servant, a tattoo that comes to life.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711190,"modifiedTime":1674268711190,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"nPfjSna6MRLAZJzC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Beast Friend","type":"power","img":"icons/environment/creatures/horses.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.i78Y7jme40GZiRcI"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This spell allows an individual to speak with and guide the actions of nature's beasts. The cost to cast is equal to the sum of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (minimum 1 per creature). Controlling five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dog / Wolf]{wolves} (Size &minus;1) costs 5 points (remember the minimum cost of 1), for example. Controlling a rhino (Size 5) costs 5 points.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the creatures obey simple commands, like a well-trained dog. They attack foes and endanger their lives for their master. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll means the beasts are more obedient. They won't kill themselves but overcome their natural fears to follow their orders.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarms} can also be controlled. Small Swarms cost 1 point, Medium Swarms cost 2, and Large Swarms cost 3.</p>\n<p><em> Beast friend</em> works only on natural creatures with animal intelligence, not humanoids, and has no effect on conjured, magical, or otherwise &ldquo;unnatural&rdquo; animals.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Bestiarium (+2): </span>The caster may affect magical and mythical beasts with animal intelligence.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+1): </span>The base Duration increases to 30 minutes per rank.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mind Rider (+1): </span>The caster can communicate and sense through any of the beasts they've befriended.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"The caster concentrates and gestures with his hands.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711043,"modifiedTime":1674268711043,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"o7GtHoHXwoSg2kH2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Curse","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/unholy/hand-light-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.CM2HSrI2xwaB4zeA"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Some practitioners of the arcane arts heal their allies. Others inflict sickness upon their enemies. To use this particularly nasty spell, the caster makes an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the victim's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll. Failure means the victim suffers a level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} immediately and at sunset each day thereafter (further castings of <em>curse</em> have no additional effect).</p>\n<p>Once the accursed becomes @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, he makes a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} roll each day to avoid death.</p>\n<p><strong>Breaking the Curse:</strong> The <em>curse</em> can be lifted by the original caster at will, and ends automatically if she's slain. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</em> also removes a <em>curse</em> (at &minus;2), though each individual may only try once&mdash;if failed it's beyond her abilities.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Turn to Stone (+5): </span>The accursed suffers a level of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} each round instead of each day. When @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, the victim turns to stone and is considered an object.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Effigy, ritualistic words, vile curse spoken","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711243,"modifiedTime":1674268711243,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"oVdxR8KBpAx6yANH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y6l3qfj0w3","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000","name":"Heroic","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_e37lp7g17kg"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["7vEypESjFOGQX3cG","aRumBWgybWwDmjdn","OQNwG8oyOYksAnbN"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","system":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipStatus":1,"isArcaneDevice":false,"arcaneSkillDie":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"powerPoints":{},"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"category":"","damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"parry":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false,"trademark":0,"isHeavyWeapon":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711006,"modifiedTime":1674268711011,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"pTFkKCHFB7POLJBr"}
{"name":"Havoc","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/lightning/bolt-strike-explosion-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.H5MaRBwwdqNVelwo"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This ability creates chaos and mischief for all those within its area of effect, hurling debris and rivals in all directions.</p>\n<p>With success, the caster places a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} anywhere within @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{range}, or a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} emanating from the caster.</p>\n<p>Anyone touched by the template is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} and must <em>then </em>make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength} roll (at &ndash;2 if the caster got a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}). Those who fail are hurled [[/r 2d6]]&Prime;&mdash;directly away from the caster if using the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} or directly away from the center if using a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Blast Template} (the caster chooses for those in the dead center).</p>\n<p>Victims who strike a hard object (such as a wall) take [[/r 2d4]] damage (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal} unless it's a spiked wall or other more dangerous hazard).</p>\n<p><strong>Airborne Targets</strong>: Flying or airborne targets suffer an additional &minus;2 to their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength} rolls as they have no ground to brace themselves on.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+1): </span><em>Havoc </em>affects a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Havoc (+2): </span>Targets are knocked back a total of 3d6\" and take 2d6 damage if they strike a hard object.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Whirlwind, chaotic poltergeists, repulsion field","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711118,"modifiedTime":1674268711118,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"q2jH1qYm4A7y6wAy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Blind","type":"power","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/moulinette/tiles/custom/icons-custom/feats/feats/blind-fight.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.y5NOIeowHKsJZtw9"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>School: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.8 Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>Those affected by this malicious power suffer blurred vision or near-complete blindness with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the victim suffers a &minus;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} to all actions requiring sight, or &minus;4 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p>The victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} roll as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} removes 2 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties}, and a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Area of Effect (+2/+3): </span>For +2 Power Points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Strong (+1): </span>The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} roll to shake of the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Bright flash of light, sand in eyes, confusion","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711047,"modifiedTime":1674268711047,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"q6RqNW5PAdTYxvK0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
