{"name":"Telekinesis","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/light/hand-sparks-smoke-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.bK9bmMuzxxskuPkj"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Telekinesis </em>is the ability to move objects or creatures (including oneself) with arcane will. It has a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength} of d10, or d12 with a raise.</p>\n<p>Unwilling opponents resist the caster's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll when targeted and at the start of each of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{turns} afterward until they're released. They can be moved up to the caster' @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} per turn in any direction, and can be bashed into walls, ceilings, or other obstacles for Str+d6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage}.</p>\n<p>Dropped creatures suffer @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Falling]{falling damage} as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Telekinetic Tools</strong>: A caster can wield tools (including weapons) with <em>telekinesis </em>as an action. Use the caster's relevant @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{skill} when attacking in this way (not his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+3): </span>The Strength of telekinesis is d12, or d12 + 2 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. Objects weighing 1,000 pounds or more automatically deal @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage]{damage} when used as weapons.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"5","trapping":"A wave of the hand, magic wand, steely gaze","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711297,"modifiedTime":1674268711297,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"uKF2SSx39KYm3gDP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Divination","type":"power","img":"icons/commodities/materials/glass-orb.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.rW9BcVUSfjVHtCke"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Divination </em>allows the caster to contact otherworldly beings to gain information.</p>\n<p>Preparing the spell takes one uninterrupted minute of prayer, coaxing or otherwise communing with a spirit or deity. Once that's done, the caster makes her @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll. Success means the entity answers the character's questions to the best of its ability. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} means the spirit is more helpful, knowledgeable, or direct than usual (whether it wants to be or not).</p>\n<p>Answers are typically vague or symbolic rather than direct&mdash;they provide clues and guidance rather than spoilers that ruin a mystery or adventure.</p>\n<p>The type of entity contacted determines how it communicates. Spirits in the netherworld tend to know only those things pertinent to their life and death&mdash;and they may not even know the identity of their killer if the person was masked or unseen.</p>\n<p>Likewise, nature spirits know only about their local environs, demons know only about the affairs they're directly involved in, and so on. The Dungeon Master must decide what the entity knows based on its background, origin, and personality.</p>\n<p>Once a spirit has been conversed with it may not be contacted again for 24 hours. The Dungeon Master may extend this to a community of spirits in a single place, such as water spirits in a babbling brook or nameless spirits in a mass grave.</p>\n<p><strong>Sacred Ground:</strong> Contacting a spirit on ground sacred to it (a deep forest for fey creatures, a temple for deities, a volcano for fire elementals or infernals, etc.) adds +2 to the roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Power (+3): </span>This modifier works only on ground sacred to the entity the caster is attempting to contact&mdash;a deep forest for fey creatures, a temple for deities, a volcano for fire elementals or infernals, etc. The being may even manifest or appear in some form with a raise.\n<p>The entity not only answer the petitioner's questions but also offers unsolicited advice. Exactly what and how it's delivered depends on the entity. Woodland creatures may warn the caster about a dangerous area of the forest. A demon might gloat that a greater threat lies ahead, accidentally tipping some other entity's hand in a later encounter.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"A brief conversation of about five minutes","trapping":"Seances, prayers, demonic interrogation.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711256,"modifiedTime":1674268711256,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"undU5Bc4pj3ZkQCD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Speak Language","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.4yWdHzffWGODxsr5"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This power allows a character to speak, read, and write a sapient language other than his own. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll allows the user to appropriately use and understand slang and dialect as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Beasts (+1): </span>Allows the caster the speak and understand any animal or vermin. The knowledge and awareness is limited by their intelligence.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Speak Language (+2): </span>The caster can speak, read, and write all sapient languages at once.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Plants (+2): </span>Allows the caster to speak and understand any plant. The sentientence of plants would limit the kinds of information they can convey.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Mass Understanding (+5): </span>The caster causes characters within @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts} &times;2 of him to understand one another, regardless of language.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Words, pictures, hand motions","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711182,"modifiedTime":1674268711182,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"v15t9Hv0aduYeYKN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Darksight","type":"power","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/5f43f8ea1a91d63438d13159/moulinette/tiles/custom/icons-custom/feats/feats/blinding-critical.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.mKUgFQiQwiGSSFP9"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Darksight </em>allows a hero to see in the dark. With success, he ignores up to 4 points of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{Illumination penalties}. With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, he ignores up to six points and can see in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{pitch darkness}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Greater Darksight (+2): </span>The recipient's senses extend so far into the infrared and ultraviolet spectrums that he ignores all @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Illumination]{illumination} penalties and 4 points of penalties from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisible} creatures.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Glowing eyes, dilated pupils, sonic sight","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711079,"modifiedTime":1674268711079,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"vL9vygimNak5NDAs","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Disguise","type":"power","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.AaOLRcWRLNY6bVyh"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Disguise </em>allows the target to assume the appearance of another person of the same @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} and shape, including clothing. It does not confer any abilities, however.</p>\n<p>Those who have reason to question the imposter's identity make a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at &minus;2 to see through the <em>disguise </em>(&minus;4 with a raise on the casting roll). This is a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Size (+1): </span>The recipient may assume the shape of someone up to two @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Sizes} larger or smaller than themselves. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Malleable features, illusionary appearance, hair of new form","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711251,"modifiedTime":1674268711251,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"vhfkpWfO5gEc0rqC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Invisibility","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/unholy/silhouette-light-fire-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_51jpasltq9","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Gg7upKot9PapOR6a"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>With a success, the character and his personal items are transparent except for a vague blur or outline. Any action taken against him that requires sight is made at &minus;4, or &minus;6 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. The same penalty applies to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls to detect the unseen presence.</p>\n<p>Reduce the penalty by 2 if the invisible character's position is given away, such as moving in water, hit with mud or another substance that reveals her form, outside in the rain, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+2): </span>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds. If the character attempts a damage-causing attack or targets a willing character with a power, the effect terminates immediately.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Powder, potion, iridescent lights","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711271,"modifiedTime":1674268711271,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"vmroBerFvOLZHDr0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Summon Animal","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/ox-buffalo-horned-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.9RXoXcRzUIWJN4B3"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This power channels beasts of the natural world to perform tasks or attack one&rsquo;s foes. From mighty elephants to spying rats, such creatures are powerful friends in the right circumstances.</p>\n<p>Summoned animals are loyal to the caster (but may be taken over by beast friend or similar abilities).</p>\n<p>They understand simple commands such as attack a particular target, push that rock, and so on, but are animals and act as such.</p>\n<p>Summoned animals act on the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.b0BBoKY0d5GZgOVk]{Action Card}. They (or their corpses) return from wherever they came from when the spell expires.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Animals (Varies): </span>Additional allies of the same type may be summoned at the same time for half the Power Point cost of the original summons (total cost including modifiers, rounded up).</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+1): </span><em>Summon animal's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Increased Trait (+1): </span>The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 Power Point. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Mind Rider (+1): </span>The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Summon Animal</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Animal</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Cost</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Alligator/Crocodile</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Bear</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Bird of Prey</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Boar</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Bull</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Boar</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Cat, Small</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Cat, Large</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">N</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Dinosaur (Herbivore)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">7</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Dinosaur (Aquatic)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Dinosaur (Carnivore, Small)</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">S</td>\n<td class=\"centered\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"centered\">Dinosaur (