{"name":"Leaping","type":"power","img":"icons/skills/movement/feet-bladed-boots-fire.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.BPt8sthjswgS20K8"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The target of this spell can @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{jump} greater distances than normal. A success doubles his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Movement]{jumping} distances, while a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} quadruples them. Modifiers are applied after running starts are factored in.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Powerful legs, legs change to an animal's.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711130,"modifiedTime":1674268711130,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"xqQn3GN5WNVWGLrF","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Wish","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/holy/barrier-shield-winged-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qmkdk1c7wo","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Legendary","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.v9yEHCDLrRQNSNKN"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Wish allows a character to bend reality to his will. It is taxing to alter reality, however, so the caster must permanently sacrifice 3 of his own Power Points (after the spell is cast). A raise on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll eliminates this cost.</p>\n<p>A caster may wish for any one of the following effects per casting, chosen before the roll is made:</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Activate a Power:</strong> Wish casts any other available power, including modifiers, available in the campaign with a raise. If the spell is @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed}, the target rolls with a &minus;2 penalty on top of any other modifiers. If the Power Points required to activate the power and modifiers are greater than the cost of wish, the caster must pay the difference.</li>\n<li><strong>Intercession:</strong> The caster wishes for some form of aid, which typically appears after a short period of time. A party trapped in a collapsed dungeon might wish for escape only to be rescued by a party of dwarven miners. A spellcaster could wish to know the true name of a powerful demon and be contacted the next day by a traitorous subordinate of the creature.</li>\n<li><strong>Gain an Edge:</strong> The caster can gain (or grant another) a permanent Edge. The recipient must meet the Edge's Requirements and can never gain more than one Edge from a wish.</li>\n<li><strong>Wealth:</strong> The spellcaster wishes for up to 10,000 gp worth of goods, including anything from transportation to supplies to magic items. Such goods generally sell for a quarter of their value. The wealth doesn't appear from nothing but rather comes to the caster via events contrived by the DM.</li>\n<li><strong>Travel Back Through Time:</strong> The caster travels back in time for a short period: one minute outside of combat or back to the start of the current round in combat. Everything that happened in that period is reversed except for the caster's Power Points, Bennies, and Wounds.\n<p>The DM should do her best to remember all other actors' state of things from the start of the round, but warping time is imperfect so don't worry about getting everything exactly right.</p>\n<p>Once reversed, only the caster remembers the alternate sequence of events, and that period of time cannot be altered again.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>See the Future:</strong> The caster peers into the near or far future. A look into the near future grants her three Conviction tokens that must be used by the caster or anyone she's currently in contact with (mental, verbal, in sight, etc.) within the next five rounds. At the end of the fifth round, any remaining tokens are discarded. A look into the far future allows the caster to ask the Dungeon Master one question about the future and receive as accurate an answer as possible. Actions by the spellcaster can change the future, however, so this may only be the most likely path or a warning of future dangers.</li>\n<li><strong>Raise a Trait:</strong> Wish can permanently increase a Trait one die type. This increases the Trait's limit by one die type as well. A recipient may never have more than one Trait raised by a wish.</li>\n<li><strong>Restore Fate:</strong> The hero and all Wild Cards in Range may refill their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to their usual starting maximum.</li>\n<li><strong>Special:</strong> The character may change relatively minor aspects of herself, others, or the world around her (if the subject of the wish doesn't want to be affected, it's resisted with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll at &minus;2). This shouldn't cause any far-reaching changes to the world or history, shouldn't be covered by one of the abilities above, and is completely at the whim of the Dungeon Master. A caster can change her gender, ancestry, languages, etc., but these changes do not alter time and are thus not retroactive.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Wish can improve someone's mood (and their attitude on the Reaction Table, if appropriate), but it can't permanently affect free will. It can't force a change of heart or make someone harm themselves.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Legnedary","pp":"20","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A jinn from a bottle, clicked heels, an incantation, a monkey’s paw.","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711020,"modifiedTime":1674268711020,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"yJBvKufi1V2sWiLf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Shape Change","type":"power","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/cougar-roar-rush-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.NTRkDvthXiRJbyvU"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Many spellcasting traditions have the ability to take on the shape of animals. This power does just that, allowing the caster to take the form of the following creature types: @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Animal (Type)]{Animal}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Dragon (Type)]{Dragon}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Elemental]{Elemental}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Humanoid (Type)]{Humanoid}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Plant (Type)]{Plant}.</p>\n<p>What a character can change into depends on his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Advancement]{Rank}:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"main-heading\" colspan=\"3\">Shape Change</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"sub-heading center\">Size</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Novice</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Size &minus;4 to Size &minus;1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Seasoned</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Size 0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Veteran</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Size 1 to 2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">11</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Heroic</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Size 3 to 4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">15</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Legendary</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Size 5 to 10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>With a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the roll, the character transforms into a particularly large version of its type&mdash;increase its @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor} by one die type each.</p>\n<p>Weapons and other personal effects are assumed into the animal's form and reappear when the power ends, but other objects are dropped.</p>\n<p>While transformed, the character retains his own @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Hindrances]{Hindrances}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Edges]{Edges}, and linked @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{skills} (though he may not be able to use some or all of them depending on the form&mdash;DM's call). He gains the animal's @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Strength}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Vigor}, and linked @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{skills} and cannot use devices that require humanoid form. He has no capacity for speech and cannot activate @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers]{powers}, though he may continue to maintain powers previously active.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bestiary]{creature's} natural abilities inherent to its form are conferred, but magical ones aren't. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dragon]{dragon} can fly and breathe fire in a traditional fantasy setting, for example, so a character who <em>shape changes </em>into one may do so as well. If dragons also cast spells in that world, however, <em>shape change </em>would not grant that ability because it's not inherent to the physical form.</p>\n<p><strong>Size</strong>: The caster does not inherit extra @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wounds} when transforming into creatures of Large or Huge @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Duration (+1): </span><em>Shape change's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Transform (+2/+3): </span>The power may affect others at a Range of Touch for +2 Power Points or Smarts for +3 (the Range Modifier may increase this further). Unwilling targets resist with an opposed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll and if transformed, may make another @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Traits]{Spirit} roll at the end of each of their turns to shake off the effect (at &ndash;2 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}). Otherwise, the power lasts for the normal Duration.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"\"Morphing\", talismans, tattoos","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":"","source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711170,"modifiedTime":1674268711170,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"zIIqvCcdbQ3fJluD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Relief","type":"power","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-hand-gold-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_11bmcg1878bi","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.yKszGE35p22cpWtd"},"swadesfxvfx":{"tokenMagicData":{"macrosToken":"","macroTokenDelay":"","macroTokenDuration":"","macrosTarget":"","macroTargetDelay":"","macroTargetAnimationDuration":false,"macroTargetDuration":""},"animationTemplate":"","animationDelay":"","audioTemplate":"","audioDelay":""}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><em>Relief</em> allows the caster to recover from a negative condition or the effects of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.</p>\n<p><strong>Recover: </strong>The caster removes one of the following negative conditions: @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. A @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll removes two conditions. If affecting more than one target (via the Additional Recipients modifier), the caster may choose which condition(s) to remove for each ally.</p>\n<p><em>Relief</em> can't remove negative conditions caused by ongoing effects (@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound or Entangled}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}, etc.) unless the source of the effect is removed.</p>\n<p><strong>Numb: </strong>Reduces the recipient's total penalties from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} by one with success, or two with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}. An Exhausted (&minus;2) hero with three @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} (&minus;3), for example, reduces her total &minus;5 penalty to &minus;4 with success, and &minus;3 with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</p>\n<p>This effect lasts one hour. It doesn't actually remove the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} or the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, it just allows the recipient to ignore the penalties. If the target would be @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} by @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, she's still @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{Powers} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.4 Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Additional Recipients (+1): </span>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star-icon\"><span class=\"list-heading\">Restoration (+3): </span>The caster can restore one die type from an energy draining effect with a success, two with a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">Stunned (+1): </span>If using the Recover option, the caster may also affect the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} condition. This completely removes the effects of being @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant/One Hour","trapping":"Prayer, tonics","arcane":"","ap":0,"modifiers":[],"skill":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674268711156,"modifiedTime":1674268711156,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"zQd08vP2gGEFeYqi","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
